[normal]The Impact of the 2010 Sp[bold]ending Review Settlement on Social Care[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Eligibility
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Joshua, on the effects of losing care[bold]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“I was told that I no longer met the criteria… I can dress myself but I’ve had to give up w
[normal]earing socks. I struggle with shoes and frequently have to ask friends, colleagues, family and even people on the street to rescue my shoes and put them back on when they fall off.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Amy, on what social care enables her to do[bold]:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“It’s about being able to have the same aspirations as others. I hold down a job, live independently and I 
[normal]am able to live life in the way I choose. I believe this is a fundamental right, but it has also given me an immense sense of freedom.”
